<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
====Photo Gallery====
The [[Special:MyLanguage/Inventory#Photo Gallery|Photo Gallery]] is where custom photos are located. Photos can serve multiple purposes, such as an additional profile picture option on a user's profile. They can also be used when sending invites to other users. Photos can also be used to change the banner for a group, and add to the group's gallery.
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
====Prints====
{{Thumb|{{YouTube|BCv8S-1wZpE}}|}}
[[Special:MyLanguage/Prints|Prints]] are photos users can take within VRChat and spawn as an object in-world for other users to share and save. Prints can carry metadata of: who took the photo, where, and when a photo was taken if taken in a public world and the feature is turned on in camera settings. Prints have the same appearance as real-world [[Wikipedia:Instant_film|instant films]].
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
Users can "collect" prints by saving them to their [[Special:MyLanguage/Inventory|Inventory]].
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
====User icons====
[[File:VRChat Plus Icons.webp|thumb|200x200px|User Icons can be displayed on a user's nameplate if they are subscribed to VRC+.]]
[[Special:MyLanguage/Inventory#User Icons|User Icons]] are circular images that can be equipped for both profiles and groups. When equipped to your profile, the icon is displayed on your nameplate, in the Here tab, at the top of the Quick Menu, and on your profile, replacing the free icon of the first 3 characters of your username.
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
====Custom emoji====
<!-- make sound beter plox -->
Up to nine custom [[Special:MyLanguage/Emojis#Custom stickers|emoji]] can be uploaded and used in the Inventory, providing unique expressions and reactions. Animated emoji are also supported.
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
====Custom stickers====
Custom [[Special:MyLanguage/Stickers#Custom stickers|stickers]] can be uploaded similarly to how custom emojis are. Stickers are placeable images that any user can see, only one can be placed at a time. When a user leaves an instance, their stickers will disappear. Users can hide a sticker by selecting it, blocking a user will also hide their stickers.
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
====UI decorations====
Supporters can customize UI elements to their liking, including the UI theme colors and selecting background designs for the [[Special:MyLanguage/Quick Menu|Quick Menu]] and [[Special:MyLanguage/Main Menu|Main Menu]].
</div>

